these are awful, tastless and gross. ewwww never again.

i work as a letter carrier at canada post. My job is outside in the heat all day and these container hold ice!!! its so exciting for me to find a great product, like the ice cubes are still huge at the end of the day. They dont leak and they fit in my satchel cup holder as well as cup holders in my truck. I love love love these. the only downfall is that they are not dishwasher safe, but its certainly not a deal breaker. Contigo is known for its great quality so its unlikely they will need to be replaced any time soon. I am thrilled to find a water bottle that wasnt 100 dollars plus that can still hold ice outside in the heat all day. I highly recommend these.

review_title: i love it......but definetly buy one size up
reviews:
i am 5.1 about 155lbs and after readin all the reviews they said to buy one size up. i did and im glad. so it fits perfectly. the quality is great. my girls feel like they are well supported with thicker straps which is nice. the bottoms are nice, my butt is not falling out, no wedgies and the high waist still allows you to still see my curvy figure with the rouching flatters my mommy pouch lol
im likely going to buy another one for my second suit.

we reviewed dozens of different chairs and took about 2months before we decided to buy a chair, for us its a pretty big purchase and wanted to avoid the hassle of trying to return somehthing large during covid19.
this chair is acutally really really nice. leather of good quality. my husband is not an idiot and didnt have any problem assembling the chair. it has a relcline option with foot out which is nice. it hugs you when sit in it properly. the color is vibrant and nice. we got orange and black. and there is a lumbar pillow which plugs in and vibrates if you like that. I dont, it just upsets my stomach lol but i can see how some ppl might like that. were very happy with our purchase and would recommend it to others

higher quality, nice easy adjustable straps, good suction and really is antifog. my kids have been loving this set and practice with them a lot in our pool. will definietly be taking them with us when we travel too. great set. great quality. id recommend them

they dont seem like much when you first open them.....my first thought was "may as well go commando" but they are actually pretty decent for sweat wicking and dryness. I work as a letter carrier for canada post and delivering mail in this recent heat wave has not been very pleasant. so sweat wicking anything is very important for me as my job requires me to be quite athletic. Ill be ordering more now that I know they are worth it. I recommend them, they are breathable and dont retain moisture unlike cotton.
